## Case Definition
## Confirmed Case
Clinical illness(A) with laboratory confirmation of infection:
- Isolation of Aeromonas spp in an appropriate clinical specimen (e.g., stool)(B)
## Probable Case (Outbreak Only)
Clinical illness(A) in a person who is epidemiologically linked to a confirmed aeromonas case
(A) Clinical illness is usually characterized by watery and/or bloody diarrhea and sometimes abdominal pain, fever.
(B) Refer to the Public Health Laboratory (ProvLab) Guide to Services for current specimen collection and submission information.

## Reporting Requirements
Laboratories
All laboratories shall report all positive laboratory results associated with an outbreak investigation, by mail, fax, or electronic
transfer within 48 hours (two business days) to the:
- Chief Medical Officer of Health (or designate), and
- Medical Officer of Health (or designate) of the zone.
Alberta Health Services and First Nations and Inuit Health Branch
- Report outbreaks only using the Alberta Outbreak Report Form.
- Completion of an NDR is not required.

